The King was now so much distressed that we might almost pity him , if it were possible to pity a King so shabby and ridiculous . 
His clever brother , Richard , had bought the title of King of the Romans from the German people , and was no longer near him , to help him with advice . 
The clergy , resisting the very Pope , were in alliance with the Barons . 
When the King next met his Parliament , the Barons , led by this Earl , came before him , armed from head to foot , and cased in armour . 
But , at a good time for him , his brother Richard came back . 
