Sir John was not as careful as he should have been , but encamped at Rosslyn , near Edinburgh , with his army divided into three parts . 
The Scottish forces saw their advantage fell on each part separately defeated each and killed all the prisoners . 
The Scottish cause now looked so hopeless , that Comyn and the other nobles made submission and received their pardons . 
