His head was set upon a pole on London Bridge , his right arm was sent to Newcastle , his left arm to Berwick , his legs to Perth and Aberdeen . 
Wallace will be remembered in songs and stories , while there are songs and stories in the English tongue , and Scotland will hold him dear while her lakes and mountains last . 
