The Earl of Warwick took all this pretty graciously for a man of his proud temper , until the question arose to whom the King's sister , MARGARET , should be married . 
As they were joined by great numbers of people , and as they openly declared that they were supported by the Earl of Warwick , the King did not know what to do . 
They lasted about three months . 
The King was washing his hands before supper , when some one whispered him that a body of a hundred men were lying in ambush outside the house . 
Whether this were true or untrue , the King took fright , mounted his horse , and rode through the dark night to Windsor Castle . 
Another reconciliation was patched up between him and the King Maker , but it was a short one , and it was the last . 
A new rising took place in Lincolnshire , and the King marched to repress it . 
In these dangerous circumstances they both took ship and sailed away to the French court . 
