Her second husband , SIR MATTHEW CRADOC , more honest and more happy than her first , lies beside her in a tomb in the old church of Swansea . 
The ill blood between France and England in this reign , arose out of the continued plotting of the Duchess of Burgundy , and disputes respecting the affairs of Brittany . 
The King feigned to be very patriotic , indignant , and warlike but he always contrived so as never to make war in reality , and always to make money . 
