When King Henry was making ready to renew the war in France , the French King was contemplating peace . 
That one was a pretty young girl named ANNE BOLEYN , niece of the Earl of Surrey , who had been made Duke of Norfolk , after the victory of Flodden Field . 
Anne Boleyn's is a name to be remembered , as you will presently find . 
In making interest with the King , the Duke of Suffolk had addressed his most powerful favourite and adviser , THOMAS WOLSEY a name very famous in history for its rise and downfall . 
On the accession of Henry the Eighth , he was promoted and taken into great favour . 
He was wonderfully fond of pomp and glitter , and so was the King . 
This kind of learning pleased the King too . 
Never had there been seen in England such state as my Lord Cardinal kept . 
His wealth was enormous equal , it was reckoned , to the riches of the Crown . 
His palaces were as splendid as the King's , and his retinue was eight hundred strong . 
He held his Court , dressed out from top to toe in flaming scarlet and his very shoes were golden , set with precious stones . 
Through the influence of this stately priest , a grand meeting was arranged to take place between the French and English Kings in France but on ground belonging to England . 
