The rest of the history of the Protectorate of Oliver Cromwell is a history of his Parliaments . 
His first one not pleasing him at all , he waited until the five months were out , and then dissolved it . 
The next was better suited to his views and from that he desired to get if he could with safety to himself the title of King . 
He was already as high , in England and in all the world , as he would ever be , and I doubt if he cared for the mere name . 
