The Duke of York , then residing in Scotland , had , under the law which excluded Catholics from public trust , no right whatever to public employment . 
Nevertheless , he was openly employed as the King's representative in Scotland , and there gratified his sullen and cruel nature to his heart's content by directing the dreadful cruelties against the Covenanters . 
As Cameron publicly posted a declaration that the King was a forsworn tyrant , no mercy was shown to his unhappy followers after he was slain in battle . 
